text: The total number of dangerous occurrences reported during the year was 1,409, an increase of 1ll over the total for 1959. However, the number of notifiable accidents associated with occurrences fell from 252 (31 of them fatal) in 1959 to 245 (22 fatal) in 1960. The main increase in the numbers of occurrences reported occurred in the category of those due to the collapse or failure of a crane, derrick, winch or hoist , where there was an increase of almost one-third from 335 to 438.
